Although I don‚Äôt believe that wealth makes you a certain way, I do think it amplifies who you are.

And if you come from a wealthy family that models selfish and unempathetic behavior then you will likely model that behavior as well.

Paul Piff and Dacher Keltner ran several studies looking at whether social class (as measured by wealth, occupational prestige, and education) influences how much we care about the feelings of others.

They found that ‚Äúless affluent individuals are more likely to report feeling compassion towards others on a regular basis.‚Äù

‚ÄúThese findings build upon previous research showing how upper-class individuals are worse at recognizing the emotions of others and less likely to pay attention to people they are interacting with.‚Äù

Why does wealth correlate with selfishness?

Piff and his colleagues suspect that the answer may have something to do with how wealth and abundance give us a sense of freedom and independence from others. The less we have to rely on others, the less we may care about their feelings. This leads us to be more self-focused. Another reason has to do with our attitudes towards greed. Like Gordon Gekko, upper-class people may be more likely to endorse the idea that ‚Äúgreed is good.‚Äù Piff and his colleagues found that wealthier people are more likely to agree with statements that greed is justified, beneficial, and morally defensible. These attitudes ended up predicting participants‚Äô likelihood of engaging in unethical behavior.‚Äù

Source: How Wealth Reduces Compassion, Scientific American

I share this not to say that we will all become selfish if we become wealthy. It‚Äôs to be more hyper-aware of this correlation so that you can catch yourself if you start losing perspective.

If anything, I‚Äôve become more hyper-aware of how others are suffering. I‚Äôve become more generous with my donating money and helping out family members.

However, I come from poverty. I know what it‚Äôs like to go without.

What if I had been born wealthy?

It‚Äôs not a black-and-white issue but one we should all be aware of.', 'comments': 3118, 'datetime': '2024-01-23T14:01:48.000Z', 'id': '3286643353054693683', 'image_url': 'https://instagram.faqp2-3.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t51.29350-15/420869268_1120400465614788_2594112964428897964_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_fr_p1080x1080&_nc_ht=instagram.faqp2-3.fna.fbcdn.net&_nc_cat=100&_nc_ohc=Mhq88vYzHdcQ7kNvgHvGZdn&edm=AOQ1c0wBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AYCRny84FyUV9WELS42gtVgNg-ZU5aiZ6zkj4OX_LtBe0w&oe=66B0420C&_nc_sid=8b3546', 'likes': 180343, 'content_type': 'GraphVideo'}, {'caption': 'Comment FREEDOM below to join my free investing class!
